g the key figures studied here are some of the most beloved in American photography, including Walker Evans, Ben Shahn, and Aaron Siskind.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aCollections, Catalogs, Exhibitions. 4aGeneral. 4aPhotography. 7aPhotography / Collections, Catalogs, Exhibitions / General.2bisacsh1 aBlair, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlair, Sara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLee, Anthony W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Anthony W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRosenberg, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenberg, Eric, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026566040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035245240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520352452423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520352452/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles